      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BUNGY (6) made an encouraging debut two weeks ago when he came from this barrier for second, beaten 3.3 metres at Ballarat. With natural improvement likely he could go one better. TRYX VIXEN (5) is finding it hard to win but continues to race well, adding to a string of placings when third last start at Kilmore. Raced parked but boxed on there and with a touch better luck could break through. The two juvenile outings of SHEZALLRHYTHM (2) came in the APG Melbourne Sales Graduate series, placing in a heat and finishing fourth in the final at Melton. Hasn't raced since May but should have developed with maturity and was readied with two recent trails. CAPTOTHEMAX (7) is a three-year-old gelding by Capt Midnight on debut for the Garry Graham yard. Draws wide but has been trialling well.",
